info:
MIL-DTL-38999 Series III Circular Connectors
        
        
            TE Connectivity's (TE) DEUTCH MIL-DTL-38999 Series III Standard Circular Connectors are designed for use in harsh military and aerospace environments. TE's Series III connectors offer high-density layouts with up to 187 data connections and power contacts rated up to 23A. These connectors feature triple-start couplings with anti-decoupling ratchets for high vibration applications, grounded plugs for superior EMI shielding, and 100% scoop-proof contacts for blind-mate coupling.

info:
AC Threaded Industrial Cylindrical Connectors
        
        
            Amphenol Industrial AC Threaded Industrial Cylindrical Connectors are a commercial derivative of the MIL-DTL-5015 product used in military and industrial applications. These cost-effective connectors feature a fine threaded coupling for use in benign and harsh environments. Options include more than 275 insert arrangements ranging from 1 to 55 positions and up to 150A per contact. The available arrangements enable the mixing of power and signal contacts, signal only or power only. Contacts are available in solder, crimp, or PC termination with silver or gold plating. Thermocouple and coax contacts are also available. Amphenol Industrial AC Threaded Industrial Cylindrical Connectors operate in a -55°C to +125°C temperature range.

description: Circular MIL Spec Connector 12P Sz 15 Straight Plug Socket
info:
LJT MIL-DTL-38999 Series I Connectors
        
        
            Amphenol Aerospace LJT Connectors are subminiature cylindrical connectors qualified to MIL-DTL-38999 Series I. Amphenol Aerospace LJT Connectors provide scoop-proof contact protection and grounding fingers for electromagnetic interference (EMI) shielding. A five key / keyway design eliminates mismating and ensures error-proof alternate positioning. The series is designed for use in commercial and military aerospace applications.

info:
MIL-DTL-38999 Series III Connectors
        
        
            Amphenol MIL-DTL-38999 Series III Circular Connectors deliver high-performance capabilities for demanding general duty and harsh environment applications. Developed to operate under severe high temperature and vibration, the connectors feature rapid coupling via a Tri-Start™ thread, shell-to-shell, or metal-to-metal bottoming. Amphenol designed these connectors to provide an EMI shielding capability of 65dB minimum at 10GHz and corrosion resistance of up to 500-hour salt spray exposure. Amphenol MIL-DTL-38999 Series III Circular Connectors offer a rated current range of 1.5A to 5A, a temperature range of -65°C to +175°C, minimum insulation resistance of 5000MΩ, and a dielectric withstanding voltage of 1000VRMS. These rugged and highly reliable circular connectors are ideally suited for industrial, commercial air, military, C4ISR, and space applications.

TV µCom Ethernet Connectors
        
        
            Amphenol Socapex TV µCom Ethernet Connectors are designed to address the trends of the military industry. description: Circular MIL Spec Connector 3 Contact Size 8 Wall mount Rcpt
info:
High Power Connectors
        
        
            Amphenol Aerospace High Power Connectors are designed with advanced RADial SOcKet (RADSOK®) contact technology and contact termination methods. These connectors utilize Matrix 5015 and GT-5015 connector interfaces and tooled insert arrangements for high-power applications. The connectors feature threaded or bayonet coupling, standard interfaces for utilizing existing cabling design, and gold-plated contacts for higher performance. Amphenol Aerospace High Power Connectors are available in a range of variants, including wall-mount receptacles, box-mount receptacles, straight plugs with rear access, straight plugs, jam nuts, and self-locking plug shell types. Contact styles include male thread termination, female thread termination, crimp, PC tail, and bus-bar.
